@digitalartdeal1 @patrickjamesNFT @BadgerDAO From my limited understanding of that hack/attack, it was because token approvals had been granted for the malicious wallet/contract. Those approvals would have to be granted by directly interacting with the token contract?

The biggest weakness of your assets is you. If you have expensive NFTs / ERC-20 store them in a wallet where other external contracts do not have authorisation to spend. This means all contracts including Opensea / Uniswap.
(7/7)

If you are signing a tx, know what you are signing. If you have Bored Apes in your wallet and Opensea contract is authorised to spend these tokens from that wallet, you could just be signing a private sale listing.
(6/7)
